d several times in concerts which have received high critical acclaim in the press. My last few concerts attracted audiences of more than one thousand. If the coronavirus disappears next year, I'll have recitals. If you're free then, you're more than welcome to come see. I graduated with a master's degree in bass guitar performance from a music conservatory in London. While studying there, I performed frequently in festivals, concert halls in many universities and cathedrals. Besides performing, I also do bass guitar accompaniment so I always have rehearsals with violinists, cellists, flutists, saxophonists, et cetera. I also teach bass guitar but I only teach the talented ones bevause some of the students are forced by their parents to learn to play the bass guitar which they aren't really interested in learning. They don't do much practice. Two years ago  I was interviewed on a news television channel for the first time to promote my concert. I was a little nervous since it was my first time being interviewed on television but it was an enjoyable experience. Can you play any instruments? Do you play any sports? I'm a gym lover. I go to the gym three to four times a week. I would say I'm lean and strong. I don't wanna be too big like a bodybuilder. If I were, I'd be so clumsy and my hands and fingers wouldn't ve nimble enough to pkay the bass guitar. I also enjoy hiking and playing basketball. Maybe you could be my hiking buddy. I think you're quite adventurous like me. I went bungee jumping in Macau twice. Macau Tower is the highest place in Macau. This tower is taller than any buildings in Macau. Immediately before I jumped, I was nervous and a little frightened. All the buildings and hotels including The Parisian Macao looked so short. When I was falling, it was both surreal and absolutely exhilarating. Do you like roller coasters? The most exciting roller coasters are in Fuji-Q Highland in Tokyo. Three of its roller coasters brokr the Guinness World Records. The feelings before I did a bungee jump were different to the feelings before I went on the roller coasters in Tokyo. Right before I rode those roller coasters, I felt absolutely exhilarated whereas right before I made my bungee jump, I felt nervous and scared but of course, bungee jumping was a thrilling experience. Some people are crazy about bungee jumping, whether they bungee-jump off a bridge or out of a helicopter. I'd love to go skydiving one day. It'd be a once in a lifetime experience."},{"pid":"7f308f2334e2b4a5e90b88a91e9e7ef97d84f300","tid":2237792,"uid":225921,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-11T12:43:17.000Z","msg":"有呀<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4132f0959777f50b8f3eb8fd399c5dbad02b8e23","tid":2237792,"uid":155902,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-12T08:54:55.000Z","msg":"女bass手好正<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"15543b43f6fac06ab55d0e05e41ed7988d72b08b","tid":2237792,"uid":58254,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-12T08:55:48.000Z","msg":"EPIC"},{"pid":"e7ecee81926207ecfc26a2012750cd5680e45c3f","tid":2237792,"uid":251001,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-17T17:15:28.000Z","msg":"<span class=\"gold\"><strong><span class=\"xx-large\">EPICO</span></strong></span><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q_UqztwYAOU&amp;ab_channel=Fami%E3%80%82\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DQ_UqztwYAOU%26ab_channel%3DFami%25E3%2580%2582&d=qh2qPVBUtyR5HqmPKg%2BIDL9ZTfDhdyQuSOQsORMTmv0%3D&h=8c9b2819\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q_UqztwYAOU&am